Mr. Theodore J. LeonsisMonumental Sports & EntertainmentWashington, DCHe served as chairman of Revolution Money, a digital and online payments strategy company that was acquired by American Express earlier this year, and where he continues to serve as an adviser. From 1994-2006 he held numerous senior positions with AOL, most recently as vice chairman. He previously was president of Redgate Communications Corp., which was acquired by AOL in 1993. Also is a director of NutriSystem Inc.2008 Fourth QuarterAdded to: NutriSystem Inc. - Fort Washington, PANutrisystem markets dieting products. Revenues are $418 million.















 















 










Theodore J. Leonsis: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 25, 2017 6:59 PM ET
Media

Company Overview of Monumental Sports & Entertainment, LLC



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Theodore J. Leonsis  Founder, Owner, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer , Monumental Sports & Entertainment, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 15 Board Members in 15 different organizations across 22 different industries.See Board Relationships61--
Background

		Mr. Theodore J. Leonsis, also known as Ted, is the Founder and Chairman of ViewLift, Inc. Mr. Leonsis is the Founder and Owner of Monumental Sports & Entertainment, LLC and serves as its Chairman and Chief Executive Officer. Mr. Leonsis is the Founder of Revolution LLC. He serves as a Founder and Partner at Revolution Growth. He serves as a Founder at the firm since 2011. He served as Managing Partner of Revolution Growth. He serves as Senior Advisor at RRE Ventures ... LLC. He founded SnagFilms Inc. in 2008 and serves as its Chairman. He serves as an Advisor of LaunchBox Digital. He founded Lincoln Holdings, LLC in May 1999. He served as a Strategic Advisor at Mobile Posse, Inc. He served as the President, and vice chairman of Audience business at Historic AOL LLC until January 1, 2007. Mr. Leonsis served as an Interim Co-Chief Executive Officer at Groupon, Inc., from February 28, 2013 to August 7, 2013. He served as an Advisor of Time Warner Inc. since December 31, 2006. He served as the President of the Advanced Systems Group at Time Warner Inc. He served as Special Advisor of Two Harbors Investment Corp. since October 2007. He was the Founder of Redgate Communications Corporation, where he is credited with having coined the phrase "new media". He served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Redgate Communications Corporation. He was employed at AOL from November 1993 to December 2006. He served as the President of Interactive Properties Group at Time Warner Inc. from March 1999 to January 2001. He served as the President of America Online Studios from November 1996 to March 1999, vice chairman, and president of AOL Core Services, and president of AOL Web Properties. He served as President of America Online Services Company, also a division of Time Warner Inc. from 1994 to 1996. Mr. Leonsis served as a Strategist and visionary of Historic AOL LLC. He was a mentor to dozens of successful AOL executives. Mr. Leonsis was known as AOL's "champion of the member" and was responsible for delivering a world-class experience for AOL's members in today's Multiband environment. He oversaw the core AOL service and led efforts to develop cutting-edge products and programming across its narrowband, broadband, wireless and voice services and oversaw efforts to capitalize on growth opportunities in advertising, search and commerce. Currently, he serves as a co-executive chairman of aXiomatic eSports. He has been Chairman of Lincoln Holdings, LLC since May 1999. Mr. Leonsis serves as the Vice Chairman of DC 2024; FedBid, Inc.; and Potomac School Futures Campaign. He serves on the board of Bedrock Manufacturing. He has been a Lead Independent Director of Groupon, Inc. since November 3, 2015. He has been an Independent Director of Groupon, Inc. since June 2009 and American Express Company since July 2010. He has been a Member of U.S. Advisory Board at Sportradar AG since October 27, 2015. He has been a Director of FedBid, Inc. since January 17, 2012. He serves as a Director of Resonate Networks, Inc.; MEVIO, Inc.; CustomInk, LLC, Optoro, Inc., Clearspring Technologies, Inc. and Georgetown University. Mr. Leonsis serves on the board of governors for the NBA and NHL. He served as the Chairman of AddThis, LLC. He served as the Chairman of Clearspring Technologies, Inc. and FedBid, Inc. since January 17, 2012. Mr. Leonsis served as Chairman of Serve Virtual Enterprises, Inc. He served as the Chairman of Groupon, Inc. from August 5, 2013 to November 3, 2015. He served as Vice Chairman at Groupon, Inc. from April 2011 to August 7, 2013. He served as Vice Chairman of Historic AOL LLC (alternate name, AOL LLC) until December 31, 2006 and also served as its Vice Chairman Emeritus. Mr. Leonsis served as a Director of Rosetta Stone (UK) Limited and MediaBank, LLC. He served as a Director of Bridgevine Inc. since February 2008, Proxicom, Inc. since 1999 and Preview Travel, Inc. since June 1985. Mr. Leonsis served as an Independent Director of Rosetta Stone Inc. from December 7, 2009 to May 23, 2013 and NutriSystem, Inc. from December 16, 2008 to June 6, 2012. He served as the Mayor of Orchid, Florida. Through his Leonsis Foundation, he is active in supporting such organizations as Hoop Dreams, Best Buddies, YouthAIDS, See Forever Foundation and Venture Philanthropy Partners. Mr. Leonsis is a pioneer of the Internet and new media, a sports team owner and an innovator in the world of philanthropy. He participated in launches of the Apple MacIntosh, the IBM PC and Wang office automation and founded four computing magazines. Mr. Leonsis is the producer of three documentaries feature Nanking, Kicking It and A fighting Chance. His book "The Business of Happiness: 6 Secrets to Extraordinary Success in Work and Life" was published in February 2010. He has been named one of the 25 most powerful people in sports by Sporting News and businessman of the year by Washington Business Journal, one of the 20 most influential people in sports, and one of the top 10 entrepreneur of the year. Mr. Leonsis holds a B.A. in American Studies from Georgetown University in 1977, and a graduate of Lowell High in 1973.Read Full Background




